Dec 10, 2020 Roughly cleaned up the top surface of the chest lid. Got 5 planes to sharpen before completing this.
Dec 11, 2020 Planes all sharpened. Problem with the big try plane would seem to be due to a hogback effect on the blade from sharpening it from both sides. Solution seems to be to use the coarse stone to flatten it with the blade at right angles to the stone. It's now closer to being flat, but still a little way to go. (Caution doing this. All too easy to slice the heel of the palm) Smoothing plane has similar symptoms (corners not touching the stone), but in this case it's likely to be the result of a seriously cupped sharpening stone at some time in the past. Finished flattening the toolchest lid.
