Feb 7,  2021 Cut 3 planks for the drawer fronts. Chamfered the edges of the kerfing saw fence. Resawing was done with the big ripsaw I made. Seems to be cutting pretty straight now after I took a tiny bit of set off the left hand side. Also being careful to only cut a triangle and then reverse the wood and cut from the other side helps. Even if the cut is wandering a little it won't ruin anything until the cut goes past the triangle.
