Apr 20, 2021 Cut the kerf and sawed the 3rd plank. 3-3/4in x 46-1/2in. The saw cut took 1 hour and 50 mins, didn't time the kerf cut (1.6 in^2/min)
Apr 21, 2021 Cut another section from the same beam for use as drawer bottoms.
Apr 22, 2021 Cut the kerf and sawed a plank from a piece of Bang Lang, 3in x 35in. Sawing took 15mins (7 in^2/min), kerf? Not sure. 15mins including much faffing. that other stuff may not be Bang Lang. The colour is similar, but its harder and the grain is tighter and has less detail. Cut the kerf for another piece of it 3-7/8in x 22in, took 10 solid minutes. Started to saw it and spent 30 mins before siesta time stopped me. Managed about 80% of it.
Apr 23, 2021 Completed yesterdays cut, took another 9 mins (2.2 sqin/min). Cut the kerf (10mins ish) and sawed another plank. 31mins (2.75 sqin/min) It seems that part of the reason this wood is so slow is the saw sticks. Not enough to jam, but enough to support the weight of the saw and prevent it cutting to full efficiency. Waxing the teeth (not the sides of the blade) helps. Needs to be done every 20 or so strokes. With a bit of care it could be done without even breaking rhythm. Considering running melted wax into the kerf so it happens automatically.
Apr 24, 2021 Cut another plank. Tried rubbing wax into the kerf before sawing, but it didn't seem to help. Regular touch of wax on the backstroke of the saw did though.
Messed up the timing, not sure how long this plank took, but it definitely felt easier, if not actually faster. Started looking for some blade stock to make a new kerfing saw blade. Will use the offcut from the last one. It's too short (the original was cut down from a piece bought for the bowsaw which is slightly less than double the blade length of the kerfing saw) This hopefully wont make much difference.
Apr 25, 2021 No sawing today, but started cutting the teeth for the new kerfing saw blade. This one will have a less aggressive angle (12degrees instead of 0degrees) to see if that makes it easier to push. I will also give it a little more set when I get to that stage.
Apr 26, 2021 Completed the new blade for the kerfing saw.
Apr 27, 2021 New blade cuts a lot easier. I think it is because there is more set (possibly a little too much, the kerf is visible on the completed plank) I suspect the old blade will work ok, and be a little faster, just given a bit more set.
Apr 28, 2021 Cut 2 drawer bottom planks. Not actually much faster, but easier going. Using longer reps (100+) and no noticeable decrease in accuracy.
Apr 29, 2021 Sharpened jack and try planes, and prepared the surfaces of the pieces cut for the last 4 drawer bottom pieces. Sawed the 8th piece, still almost 30 mins (2.9 sqin/min)
Apr 30, 2021 Cut the last pieces for the drawer bottoms.
