Apr 25, 2022 Cut the haunch on the front tenon and fitted the joint. Sharpened and set the infill shoulder plane. Really tricky to do, the end of the blade needs to be at exactly the right angle, which isn't exactly 90° as far as I can tell. Also there is a slight rounding on one side of the mouth that makes it look like it is wider on one side. That confuses the issue a bit. Best ignore how wide the mouth looks and just sight along the sole to see how much the blade protrudes.
