Jun 22, 2022 Prepared face side and face edge on the bottom horizontal piece. Concentrating on controlled movements. This is tricky, momentum can help start a heavy cut and it's not possible to know just how much force a given cut will take until it starts actually cutting. Ordered a flywheel and a temporary pulley, plus some flanges that may do for the headstock pulley boss and faceplates. 
Jun 23, 2022 Reduced bottom horizontal piece to width and thickness, marked out the length.
Jun 24, 2022 Cut the bottom horizontal piece to length and marked out and cut the tenons. Sunk the nut on the front of the motor mount piece.
