Jul 5,  2022 Made mars, earth and a new Neptune.
Jul 6,  2022 Tried to make some moons from the shell disks from some kind of sea snail. Drilling was not successful and trying to use the grinder to create a disc with a view to turning a groove in the edge to take the thread was also unsuccessfull. Decided to use wood and drew out some patterns for the moons and Pluto. 
Jul 7,  2022 Cut out 8 moons (1 spare) in various sizes from 6mm to 10mm
Jul 8,  2022 Started hanging planets.
Jul 9,  2022 More planet hanging, got as far as Uranus. Cats got at it at while I was sleeping after lunch. Much trouble trying to disentangle it. Galilean moons were worst hit, some will need restringing.
Jul 10, 2022 Got as far as Pluto. Also restrung using little hooks so it's easy to take it apart for packing and gives the option of stopping at mars. Completed, ready for packing. Largest piece is 26inches, too long for hand luggage. Guess that means I will be taking my rucksack after all.
Jul 11, 2022 Packed the outer planets in paper sleeves.
