Nov 28, 2022 Trimmed APL book
Nov 29, 2022 Marked out cut line on the headstock piece. Going to cut this without the aid of the kerfing plane, and the cut will be the reference surface. Used a ruler in a shallow cut on one end and sighted along the piece to mark the other end.
Nov 30, 2022 Cut the headstock piece, removing most of the crack. Squared up the face side and face edge and started marking it out.
Dec 1,  2022 Cut the headstock piece to length, width and thickness. Continued marking out and made knife walls for the tenon and screw cutting section crosscuts.
Dec 2,  2022 Cut the tenon and the recess for the screwcutting section. Drilled the bolt hole and fitted the square plate that will be the nut.
Dec 3,  2022 Trimmed the tenon so the headstock piece can sit 1 inch further to the left. Drilled and tapped the square nut. Cleaned and sharpened the tapered reamer, the one made out of jarrah with a square end that fits in a sycamore handle. Shavings were getting between the wood and the blade, andthe blade was quite rusty in places. 2 of the screws were not tightening properly so I mved the larger of them down to the smaller hole and found a new one.
Dec 4,  2022 More marking out on the headstock section. Cut the recess for the wedge. There is some rot around the area of the cup-shake. Used some superglue to help consolidate it. Looks a lot darker but I'm hoping that it will be roughly the same as the wood when it is oiled.
Dec 5,  2022 Adjusted the marking out to take account of the thickness of the brass. I want the top of the curve below the bead to be level with the outer face of the brass above it, which means the bead needs to be 3mm thicker and the curve should end 3mm further out. Deepened the recess for the nut. It is now slightly below the bottom of the recess for the wedge, which will allow for some cleanup. Cut the bearing section and the outer edge of the bead. Cut the first curve.
Dec 6,  2022 Cut the other 2 curved sides of the left hand headstock piece. Cut a wooden plate to bridge the lower surfaces of the bedways for the bolt.
Dec 7,  2022 Resawed some more wood for the right hand part of the headstock. Worked out a way to get the tailstock to fit the metal lathe. Will get some 4mm stuff to shim up the headstock and take about 2mm off the bottom of the tailstock. This will not only give a more solid tailstock than cutting it in 2 horizontaly and bolting the 2 pieces back together, but will also allow for use of 10mm or 12mm tools. These are a lot easier to find and will be more robust.
Dec 8,  2022 Cut the right hand headstock piece to length width and height. Marked it out and made knife walls for the cross-cuts that meet the final surface. Dismantled the metal turning lathe headstock so I can prepare for shimming it up. Marked out the the base of the tailstock ready for filing.
Dec 9,  2022 Marked out the right hand headstock piece and cut the bearing suupprt section.
