Dec 21, 2022 Filed the first 2 pieces to shape.
Dec 22, 2022 Adjusted the countersinking of all holes and refined the shape of the screw tabs on the first 2 bearing covers. Filed the other 2 pieces to shape.
Dec 23, 2022 Removed the headstock pieces and started flattening the bedways using the granite plate. Caught my middle finger between the granite and the spacer block. Will probably lose the nail.
Dec 24, 2022 More flattening. Almost there, probably another day to go. Started trying to remove the worn out abrasive from the other side of the granite plate. Hard going, the glue is strong (contact adhesive). I think I will try aninal glue next time, it doesn't need stick that well given the huge surface area and small sideways force. The fabric based abrasive is even harder to remove. Managed to loosen a few inches either end, which should work well as handles as I complete the sanding of the bedways.
Dec 25, 2022 More flattening, only 5 sets of 50 today. Still got a little way to go.
Dec 26, 2022 More flattening. 10 sets of 50. Low point on the nearside edge of the front bedway is now gone. Still got a low spot on the back edge of the front bedway at the right hand end, and a low spot at each end on the uprights. These are outside the useable area of the bedways but it would be nice to get them flat.
