Jan 3,  2023 Cut the slot for the shaft in the inside right bearing cover. Flattened the bottom surface of the right hand headstock piece and marked the recess for the bearing piece.
Jan 4,  2023 Started flattening the bottom of the left hand headstock piece. Another 5 sets of 50 flattening the bedways. Still a little bit more to do although I wouldn't be too unhappy to use it as is. The low spots are negligeable, or outside the useful area.
Jan 5,  2023 Started work on the tailstock for the metal lathe. Cut a piece of 14x14 steel for the guide rail. Drilled lots of holes, including the 60°one for the mounting bolt. Tilted the drill press table and bolted the tailstock down. Set the angle initially to avoid skid, then adjusted it to the correct angle once the bit was in deep enough. Drilled and tapped the guide piece. Managed to break a tap in the 3rd hole, guess I was getting careless by that point. Got it out eventually. Managed to turn it a bit, but then it stuck. Shattered a few pieces off it then drove it back out. Carried on then with the second tap (taper tap was the one that broke) and the resulting thread is fine.
Jan 6,  2023 Drilled and sawed the last 2 holes in the tailstock base. The ones that overlap with the pre-drilled ones. Snapped my only junior hacksaw blade, so I finished off by cleaning up and sharppening the tiny cold chisel and using that. Then filed the rest out. Did some more eork on flattening the base of the left hand headstock piece.
Jan 7,  2023 Finished flattening the base of the left hand headstock piece. Cleaned up the recess for the bearing retainer plate on the right hand headstock piece and screwed the plate on.
Jan 8,  2023 Cut the recess for the inner bearing retainer plate on the left hand headstock piece.
Jan 9,  2023 Finished the recess, trimmed the top edge of the plate to size and screwed it on. Cut the outer bearing retaining plate slot for the right hand headstock piece. Marked and cut the recess and screwed it on. Started restoring the old paint scraper.  Cut and drilled the scales. Screwed them in place and started shaping.
Jan 10, 2023 Completed shaping the paint scraper handle.
Jan 11, 2023 Started work on the metal lathe alterations. Cut the aluminium spacers 
Jan 12, 2023 Finished fitting the spacers and reassembled the headstock.
Jan 13, 2023 Started work on the tailstock. Looks like there will be around 2.5mm to remove, but will re-measure once the base is roughly flat. Started chiseling.
Jan 14, 2023 Tailstock base roughly flattened. Still about 2mm too high. Started trying to do some heavy removal with the cold chisel. Rough estimate of 1 week of solid hammering to remove this 2mm layer.
Jan 15, 2023 Dismantled the flywheel shaft and recut the thread on the flywheel. It was damaged by overtightening the bolt that was holding it, causing the end of the bolt to swell and stick as I removed it. It had come out ok, but the new grubscrew didn't go in easily. Filed up the T nut to fit the gap in the metal lathe bedways, and made an angled spacer washer for the head of the bolt that will hold down the tailstock. As it is, it is causing the tailstock to mover forward slightly rather than pulling it back as it should. A spacer under the front edge fixes that, so I have the rough dimensions now to make another. I will wait until the tailstock lower surface is reduced enough for it to line up with the headstock before making a new spacer waasher. Found some stock to make a copy of the stool in "Beginning Japanology, Sashimono woodwork". Started prepping it.
Jan 16, 2023 Marked up and cut the pieces for the stool. Got the taper the wrong way round, but decided to continue. Goes together nicely and I think I can recover from the mistake. Have still to do the locking bar but it is already fairly sturdy and reasonably comfortable. Do need to round of the corners a bit though. The side plane works quite well but has a tendancy to cut a lateral groove. A fence with a sloping face would fix this nicely. There may be enough left of the 10x50 brass bar to make one once I have made the bearing retainer top pieces for the lathe headstock.
Jan 17, 2023 Added an inlet piece to fix the wrong taper. Cut the recess for the locking bar. Started cutting the slots for the locking bar.
Jan 18, 2023 Finished the slots for the locking bar, and the matching slots in the locking bar. Fitted the dovetail bars on the sides of the legs. Rounded the corners, cleaned it all up and oiled it.
Jan 19, 2023 Started looking at the Hurdy Gurdy again. Will keep the back and just fill the small worm holes. Found a piece for the edge where the soundboard will mount, and a possible piece for the top bars. Cleared out a load of scraps so it is easier to find the good stuff.
