Feb 3,  2023 Cut the lower curves of the first 2 top ribs, made the soundposts and glued them in. Started looking for soundboard stock. I have some old drawer bottoms that look like top quality spruce. Should be enough there.
Feb 4,  2023 Flattened the upper surface of the hurdy gurdy body. Filled the worm holes with super glue and sawdust. Marked out the crank shape on the brass blank.
Feb 5,  2023 Cut out the crank with the jewelers saw. Broke a few blades but they cut fairly well. Filed it up, looks pretty good.
Feb 6,  2023 More flattening of the lathe bedways (500 reps). Still very small marks from the toothing plane on the bedways, a scratch at the headstock end and a small low patch at the tailstock end. It's flat enough. Finished removing the old abrasive cloth from the granite plate. That was hard work, but got a bit faster with the right technique.
Feb 7,  2023 Made a template for the lower frame members of the lathe.
Feb 8,  2023 Cut the lower frame members. Didn't dismantle the lathe, just tipped it onto it's back. It has enough mass that a bench and vice were just not needed. Good job, I'm reluctant to take it appart. Not sure if it will go back together again in exactly the same position and I don't want to have to resurface the bedways.
Feb 9,  2023 Marked out the brass bearing caps and drilled the holes for the hinges. Drilled a 9.8mm hole to provide the curved surface to fit with the other hinge pieces. Sawed the pieces to length and cut the waste away from the top surface with the hacksaw.
Feb 10, 2023 Started filing the curve into one of the top surfaces. Gave up and went to buy some new files (also a 1kg hammer and a blowtorch)
Feb 12, 2023 Finished the roughing out of the front and back curves on one bearing cover piece and started on the second one.
Feb 13, 2023 Finished roughing out the front and back curves on the second bearing cover piece.
Feb 14, 2023 Refined the front and back curves on the bearing cover pieces and started work on the hinge inner curve. Found a piece to make the nut slot cover. Attempted some engraving. Freehand is no good, need a stop or the chances of over-running the cut are too high.
Feb 15, 2023 Made the cover plate for the nut slot in the front headstock piece. Engraved the year in roman numerals MMXXIII. Screwed the blank to a piece of wood and used the machinists clamp to hold a piece of wood against the horizontal line as a stop. Recessed the headstock for it and screwed it in place. Used the granite sanding plate to flatten the surface. Had to redo the engraving as this took most of it away.
Feb 16, 2023 First attempt at a hinge piece. Works well, new blowtorch anneals the brass easily and hammering the brass around the 3mm pin is not too hard. I misscalculated the expected OD. I thought I had bought 3mm brass, but it is 2mm. The 9.8mm holes I drilled in the top piece are too large. Not a big deal, but it would be nice to have a fairly close fit. Will redo the hinge piece with 5mm rod instead. It will bring the OD back to the expected size. Looking at the length required for the hinge roll, it seems to have stretched by about 6mm. OD is 7mm, expected length with no stretching of the outer surface would be about 22mm. Actual length seems to be about 16mm. I marked a series of lines at 5mm intervals before starting to roll the hinge. The back fold at the end of the roll is somewhere between the 25mm and 20mm lines
Feb 17, 2023 Made a new hinge piece. Well acually it's the other end of the same one. Has a 5mm pin and the hinge fold ended up at around the 25mm line on the blank, so it looks like it only stretched by about 3mm I think.
Feb 18, 2023 Made 3 more hinge pieces.
Feb 19, 2023 Planed beam for the second sash cramp to size. Needed multiple sharpennings. Whatever it is, it is hard and has white streaks init which I guess could be silica.
Feb 20, 2023 Squared up and sawed a 2in by 3in piece out of a length of 4in by 2-1/2in beam for the end block of the 2nd sash cramp. Drilled the hole for the screw. Lots of gouge work, the only bit large enough to do the job is the adjustable one, which wont go in very far before the cross piece hits the surface.
Feb 21, 2023 Cut the joint for the sash cramp.
Feb 22, 2023 Cut the notches in the sash cramp bar and glued up the two pieces. Also glued the nuts in on both sash cramps.
Feb 23, 2023 Got the metal lathe working again with the raised headstock. Cleaned up the external clutch mechanism. Started turning the pin for the 2nd sash cramp.
Feb 24, 2023 Completed the pin for the 2nd sash cramp, made the base plate and twisting footrest. Assembled it all.
Feb 25, 2023 Cut some more of the grooves in the tailstock base plate using the new cold chisel.
Feb 26, 2023 Not much today. Tried to figure out if the piece of metal for the circular cold chisel is hardened or not. Seems not, but I will grind it rather than file it I think.
Feb 27, 2023 Started work on cleaning out the corners of the hinge joints on the bearing covers. Recorded it.
Feb 28, 2023 More work on cleaning the hinge corners, and another recording done closer using the mic stand as a tripod. One bearing cap is now ready for fitting to the hinge pieces.
Mar 1,  2023 Fitted the pins for one of the bearing caps.
Mar 6,  2023 Did a little more work on the tailstock base. The grooves on one half are down to the right level now.
Mar 7,  2023 Fitted the first headstock cap hinge pieces together and rounded the cap piece to match the side piece.
Mar 8,  2023 Cut another groove (the 4th) in the tailstock base. It will need a little more work to get to full depth.
Mar 9,  2023 Cut 2 more grooves. Starting to get larger and more even chips. 
Mar 10, 2023 Decided to cut another groove in between the existing ones. Gut the first of these (the 7th) and cut the first of the separating walls away.
Mar 11, 2023 Removed the second separating wall. Cut the next groove and removed 2 more separating walls. One side is now roughed out.
Mar 12, 2023 Fitted the second hige on the first bearing cover for the lathe headstock,
Mar 13, 2023 Prepared a strip of 1/4 by 3/4 to try out a possible solution to the puzzle joint.
Mar 14, 2023 Cut the pieces and assembled a trial version of the puzzle joint.
Mar 15, 2023 A little more cold chisel work on the metal turning lathe tailstock base.
Mar 16, 2023 Filming how to use a cold chisel
Mar 17, 2023 Completed the roughing out of the tailstock base and started refining it. It sits a bit high, maybe 1mm
Mar 18, 2023 Continued refining the underside of the metal lathe tailstock.
Mar 19, 2023 A little more refining. Set up the tailstock again to check for amount of vertical offset. Looks like about .84mm
Mar 20, 2023 And a little more refining.
Mar 21, 2023 More refining.
Mar 22, 2023 More refining.
Mar 23, 2023 More refining.
Mar 24, 2023 Reassembled the tailstock and removed the abrassive paper from the bedways. Marked out a new piece of steel for the sloping washer.
Mar 25, 2023 Cut the sloping washer and tested out the tailstock. Managed to break a centre drill but successfully turned an old bolt into a handle for the second sash cramp. The tailstock needs some more refining, it is pretty accurate with the rotating centre in and minimal extension, but the drill chuck is longer and needs the tailstock to be srewed out further and the point of the drill ends up about 1mm low. Oiled the second sash cramp.
Mar 27, 2023 Put the lathe parts back together and changed speed to the fastest. Turned up a point to use to check alignment. The faster speed makes quite a difference to the finish. For such small pieces (I used a piece of an old 14mm bolt) the faster speed makes sense and it isn't at all scary, not with the clutch.
Mar 28, 2023 More refining work on the base of the tailstock. There was a high point about 2/3 of the way back. The front half made good contact, but it was causing a slant that meant the alignment got worse the further the tailstock was extended. removed that and the tailstock point is now a little high (as expected). Did some more refining work using the chisel, scraper and file. Covered the surface in marker pen and slid it back and forth on the bedways to monitor progress. 
Mar 29, 2023 Finished off the base of the tailstock. Used the scraper quite a bit. It can give quite a good surface, especially with a nicely sharpened edge. It works ok straight from the grinder, but leaves a better surface if it is honed too.  The centres now align nicely, tested by trapping a ruler between them. It stands perpendicular on both axes. Cut a slice off the bottom of one of the 14mm parting tools so that now fits in the tool holder. Found a tin for the bits and spacers I can use, including a newly cut 4mm full length spacer. Drilled a hole in the vice base to fix it to the wooden base so I can use the mounting hole to bolt it to the bench. Broke a screw, I had forgotten just how hard that base piece is. Got it out using the small metalwork vice to grip the protruding part. Used a bolt and a threaded insert instead.
Mar 30, 2023 More work on the second bearing cap cover. Bought some bolts so I can hold the metalwork vice down at 2 points instead of relying on just one and the weight. Now it should stay put under heavy hammering and will look better on video.
Mar 31, 2023 Recorded video of the process clearing the corners if the hinge joints on the bearing cover caps.
Apr 1,  2023 Fitted one of the strap parts for the second bearing cap and roughly shaped the cylindrical part of the cap to match the strap.
Apr 2,  2023 Fitted the second strap part to the second bearing cap.
Apr 3,  2023 Cut the strap parts to length and cleaned up both headstock pieces ready for fitting the caps.
Apr 4,  2023 Drilled the strap piece attatchment holes and fitted the first one.
Apr 5,  2023 Fitted the other 3 strap pieces. Had to remove some of the carefully made hinge parts where the strap fits to the cap so that it can be opened by pulling out one of the hinge pins. Cleaned up the faces of the front and back of the left hand headstock piece.
Apr 6,  2023 Finished cleaning up the left hand headstock piece with file and 240 grit paper. Oiled it.
Apr 7,  2023 Cleaned up the right hand hesdstock piece and oiled it. Also oiled the left hand piece and the bedways.
Apr 8,  2023 Rough cut the sides of the left hand headstock piece bearing cap. Cut clearance on the right hand headstock piece bearing cap so I can open it by removing the pin. Oiled both pieces again.
Apr 9,  2023 Cut the sides of the other bearing cap and refined both.
Apr 10, 2023 Oiled both parts and glued a locating piece to the piece that goes on the bottom end of the bolt securing the right hand headstock piece. Cleaned out the glue pot.
Apr 11, 2023 Polished the headstock pieces and tried out the dial gauge on the lathe. Not sure whether to use the metal lathe or the new lathe to turn the headstock shaft. It will need to be set up very precisely on the metal lathe.
Apr 12, 2023 Played with setting up the shaft on the metal lathe. Set up a carrier as it is too long for the tailstock. Accuracy is not good enough.
Apr 13, 2023 New chuck arrived so I fitted that. Decided to turn down the boss on the backplate rather than use a spacer plate, which means the old chuck will not locate positively if I put it back. Accuracy is much improved, but I will probably still use the new lathe to turn it's own headstock shaft.
Apr 14, 2023 Started making a converter so I can attatch the cross slide to the new lathe. Will be 2 pieces, one bolted to the cross slide and the other locating in the bedways. The bolt that holds them to the bedways will pass through both. Once it is all adjusted correctly I will glue them together, but that can wait until the headstock shaft and bearings are complete.
Apr 15, 2023 Made the bottom part of the cross slide converter.
Apr 16, 2023 Fitted the 2 pieces, made a bottom plate and cut the bolt to length. It's not complete, but is now useable.
Apr 17, 2023 Cleaned up the bearing cavities. There were 2 screws that were a bit longer than the others that needed to be filed to length, and a hole to be plugged. Also marked the level of the centre line of the shaft so I know when to stop pouring the lead.
Apr 18, 2023 Fixed the broken marking gauge, turned it into a pencil gauge. Marked out and started cutting the bottom plate for attaching the cross slide. Adjusted the top slide shims, then put the cross slide back on the metal lathe.
Apr 19, 2023 Moved the lathe outside ready for pouring the bearings. Cut a 1.5kg diving weight up ready for melting.
Apr 20, 2023 Poured the lower bearings. Used the pottery bbq to help heat the laddle holding the lead. Probably not necessary, it melts quickly and easily with the blowtorch. Completed the bottom plate for attaching the cross slide.
Apr 21, 2023 Poured the first top bearing half. Started rearranging the workshop, put the bench against the wall to the left of the door (going in)
Apr 22, 2023 Poured the second top bearing half. Brought the lathe back in.
Apr 23, 2023 Painted the crankshaft bearing housings, the metal lathe tailstock and the bushes for the eccentric drive. Did some finishing on the frame, and sraped the bedways to remove the graphite that got spilt and was darkening it. At some point I may use graphite on the bedways, but for now I like the look of the wood grain. Cut a curve in the cabinet scraper holder so I don't have to mess about with shims to put a curve into the blade.
Apr 24, 2023 More frame finishing and oiling
Apr 25, 2023 More frame finishing and oiling
Apr 26, 2023 Replaced the flywheel and shaft.
