May 7,  2023 Rip sawed all 6 tenons. Cleaned up and fitted the 1st mortice and tenon joint.
May 8,  2023 Cleaned up and fitted 4 more mortice and tenon joints.
May 9,  2023 Fitted the last mortice and tenon joint and eased all 6 so the treadle will go together.
May 10, 2023 Glued up the treadle.
May 11, 2023 Cleaned up the ends of the tenons and marked out the chamfer on the treadle. Started turning the flywheel.
May 12, 2023 More turning. Using a bungee and a piece of string didn't really work. Kicking the spokes of the flywheel does, and with a bit of practice can be reasonably efficient. Picking a spoke to kick 180 degrees early helps to enable kicking when the wheel is already turning at a moderate speed. Dismantled the lathe and made 2 more protectors for the ends of the bedways.
May 13, 2023 Drilled the holes for the top crosspiece and the treadle pivots. Made the front support for the top crosspiece and screwed it to the back of the bedway. Reasembled the lathe. getting faster at doing this.
May 14, 2023 Made the motor controller mount tray and fitted it.
May 15, 2023 Converted one of the cheap planes to a bullnose plane. The blade is a bit steeper than I would like. I opted to go bevel up as the bed is at 45 degrees which is a bit shallow for a single iron on curly grain. Doesn't feel great to use, but it does leave a nice finish. Angle is about 75°-80°. Bevel up also means there is less of the thin sides for the screws to go through so it is a little bit more robust.
May 16, 2023 Cut a 7in disc for the eccentric drive. Sharpened the bow saw crosscut blade and replaced the string which was starting to fray.
May 17, 2023 Drilled bolt holes to secure the bosses to the eccentric (only in the central position, the eccentric holes still need to be cut and drilled)
May 18, 2023 Drilled and tapped the holes in the bearing covers. Refined the curves a bit more.
May 19, 2023 More shaping of the bearing caps. Started cutting the first piece for the top surface from the old kitchen drawer bottom.
May 20, 2023 Cut some more pieces for the top surface. Not going to use the first ones cut though. There should be enough of the old kitchen table top to make it all of the same wood. Marked where the motor mount holes should go.
May 21, 2023 Dismantled the lathe and drilled the holes for the motor mount. Sunk 2 nuts in the crosspiece and adjusted it so it will sit horizontaly. Re-assembled the lathe.
May 22, 2023 Made some long 14mm bolts and mounted the motor.
May 23, 2023 Made the pivots for the treadle. Modified the lathe top-slide so it can swing further round to cut the points. Turned out it wasn't necessary, the angle of the countersink cut by the centre drill is just within the original range of the topslide. Needed doing anyway, 40° was not enough for some things.
May 24, 2023 Tapered the inside of the ferules. Fitted the first of the ferules for the treadle and chamfered one edge.
May 25, 2023 Fitted the second ferrule and completed all the chamfers. Fitted the treadle and cut one of the pivot bolts to the correct length.
May 26, 2023 Dismantled the lathe and deepened the nut recesses in the top centre piece so the new bolts for the motor mount will reach the embeded nuts.
May 27, 2023 Extended the motor cable.
