Jun 1,  2023 Cut a piece of heavy brass tube to mount the eccentric wheel on the headstock shaft. Put it all together ready to turn the chain groove in the eccentric wheel.
Jun 2,  2023 Made the cuptured nut crosspiece to secure the toolrest.
Jun 3,  2023 Drilled the treadle for the motor auctuator. Cut and tapped the pieces of the connecting rods and fixed up a temporary treadle lift using a piece of old inner tube. Initial experiments with the headstock shaft pulley I bought (to modify) didn't work well. The groove is far too wide.
Jun 4,  2023 Made 2 pieces to form a single pulley with adjustable groove width. Made a drive belt from tripled string. At first it didn't work so I cut the motor pulley groove a bit deeper and moved the headstock shaft pulley pieces closer together.
Jun 5,  2023 Tried turning the eccentric pulley. Worked for a bit, but then the belt compacted to a size that is a bit too small and it was slipping again. Made a new belt that can be opened and has 4 rather than 3 bights. First version was too uneven, it was made by twisting 2 pieces together then twisting that. Wrapped the second version by hand and it seems ok. Completed the groove and removed the eccentric.
Jun 6,  2023 Made a small collar to replace the carrier that I used for the eccentric. Set the cross slide up ready to turn the shaft.
Jun 7,  2023 Started making the spring return for the treadle. Cut the pieces and clamped them in position to get the range right.
Jun 8,  2023 Dismantled the lathe and drilled holes in the lower back bar and the treadle for the spring return.
Jun 9,  2023 Fitted the eccentric.
Jun 10, 2023 Cut the shapes of the treadle spring return. Turned a length of threaded rod for the top attachment.
Jun 11, 2023 Turned the flwheel some more. It's easier with the eccentric to push, but I may have bruised my hand doing it. Will be easier when the treadle is connected.
Jun 12, 2023 Made a wire wrap tool.
Jun 13, 2023 Welded the short drive belt and turned the back end of the headstock shaft. Cut the flats to locate external screw cutting attachments (and help hold the shaft to cut the threads on either end)
Jun 14, 2023 Faced of the working end of the headstock shaft. Screwed the 2 parts of the cross-slide base together and glued a locating bar on the lower cross-slide mounting plate.
Jun 15, 2023 Drew some guides for hand cutting the headstock shaft main thread as per Plumier. Cut a piece for the screw cutting guide block.
Jun 16, 2023 Sharpened the carbide tools with the newly arrived diamond stone. Started modifying the cast iron pulley that will be the boss for the headstock shaft pulley. Still having trouble with the parting tool, even freshly sharpened. I think it is only ok for brass, it has no rake. Ordered another with inserts that have some rake.
Jun 17, 2023 Attempted to precut the thread on the headstock shaft. Not successful, turned it off again and tried using the die. Ended up with a badly eccentric thread. I think there is enough length left to cut it off and try again. The pulley could perhaps be used as an extension of the die holder to keep it on track.
Jun 18, 2023 Started making a makeshift die guide. Opted to use wood blocks and M12 bolts rather than drill and tap the pulley.
Jun 19, 2023 Completed the die guide, cut off the bad thread, turned the last 1inch to 19mm, cut a 30° taper and recut the thread. Went straight and the chuck centres quite nicely even though it doesn't have a central boss yet, and doesn't quite reach the shoulder.
Jun 20, 2023 Completed modifying the cast iron pulley. Took a lot of thinking about cutting angles and trying different tools to separate the un-needed flange from the rest.
Jun 21, 2023 Marked out the layers of the headstock pulley. Cut most of them.
Jun 22, 2023 Finished cutting the pulley layers.
Jun 23, 2023 Glued up the 2 parts of the largest pulley layer, and drilled and glued the 2 smaller layers.
Jun 24, 2023 Drilled the larger layer, 5/8 diameter from one side, and around 2 inches diameter from the other. Turned up a locating peg from the bad thread offcut and used it to locate the largest layer in the 4 jaw chuck. Screwed the layer to the chuck plates and turned the hole to fit the boss made from an old pulley.
Jun 25, 2023 Glued the last parts of the pulley together. Marked and drilled the boss.
Jun 26, 2023 Mounted the boss. Managed to break a screw but got lucky drilling it out and used a piece of bamboo chopstick to plug it (its the one nearest the keyway). Mounted the pulley on a length of 20mm shaft in place of the headstock sheft. Turned out the centre hole. It was already at 5/8in so it didn't take long to make it 20mm. Had to clean out a little bit with the gouge so the pulley would slide all the way on the shaft. Turned the outside. Bit messy. Pulley is good but there is lots of dust and it is a bit irritating to my sinuses. Pulley is now 3½ inches wide, tapering from 2 inches to 8½ inches. This should be good for 2, 3½, 5, 6½, and 8 inch steps.
Jun 27, 2023 Completed turning the pulley.
Jun 28, 2023 Drew designs for the treadle pulley mount. Parted off the end of the headstock shaft. Not good to have the parting tool low. The workpiece climbed over the tool and jammed. Actually saw the headstock move forward a little. Nothing was loose, it must have been just the wood flexing. Raised the tool a little and completed the cut, no damage done as far as I can tell.
Jun 29, 2023 Started making a handle for 6mm square hss. Drilled a hole in a piece of 20mm diameter steel and turned it to fit some ¾inch brass tube. Squared up the hole with a file.
Jun 30, 2023 Drilled a side hole for a grub screw. Silver soldered the brass tube and the steel plug. Tried to fit one of my old cup chucks to the new spindle. The wood won't take such a fine thread. Used the cup chuck held in the 4 jaw chuck to start turning a piece of lilac for the handle.
Jul 1,  2023 Completed the handle and ground the graver end so now it has a reversible blade, graver one end, pulley groove form tool on the other.
Jul 2,  2023 Cut a piece for the tailstock and rough shaped it.
Jul 3,  2023 Cleaned up the curved surfaces on the tailstock. Drilled the bolt hole.
Jul 4,  2023 Flattened the lower surface of the tailstock so it sits correctly. Prepared drawing of the treadle pulley side plates for Tuan to make them for me.
Jul 7,  2023 Turned a pulley for the treadle. Faced off the 40mm bar offcut ready for trying to make a ¾ 16tpi internal thread.
Jul 8,  2023 Started drilling the 40mm offcut. Worked fine up to the MT2 14.5mm bit, but the 17.5mm one only got so far before the taper started to slip. There is no room in the tailstock sleeve for a plug piece with internal flats. The screw thread is pretty much the same size as the back end of the taper. A grub screw from the side might do the trick, but it will mean taking the sleeve out every time I change bits. Measured the place to put the grub screw and drilled a hole ready for tapping.
Jul 9,  2023 Tapped the hole and drilled right through so there will be 2 grub screwes. Unfortunately that removed too much metal from the original thread and I had to drill it out for an 8mm grub screw. Seems to work fine. Drilled a bit more with the 17.5, but then it stopped working. I think I reduced the clearance angle a bit too much on the last grinding. Didn't realise that was the problem at first. The outer corners are getting rounded and I reground a few times before comparing it with the 14.5 and seeing the angle was too shallow. Try again tomorrow.
Jul 10, 2023 Gave up trying to use the drill and experimented with the boring tools. Small red one worked reasonably well but I ended up wearing away quite a bit of the underside. Must watch that more closely in future. Tried the yellow one that might actually be an internal thread tool. That worked reasonably well. Cut the thread with a great deal of difficulty. Running the bottoming tap in to help relieve the taper tap seemed to help, but was alternating between the 2 roughly every half rotation.
Jul 11, 2023 Parted off a piece of the 40mm steel bar and mounted it on the new lathe. Cut the recess to allow it to locate on the 20mm part of the shaft. Fitted it and cleaned it up and cut the centre boss to help locate chucks. Seems to have worked. Not going to attempt to thread the other half. Don't like working steel much, at least not this way. Too much brute force needed. Ugly.
Jul 12, 2023 Cut a 2½inch piece of 50mm brass bar for a cup chuck mount using the hacksaw. Got the cut face pretty accurate, estimate ±0.1mm. Faced it and drilled and tapped the hole. Much easier in brass than in steel. Had to regrind the 17.5 drill, but it cut ok. Parted off a piece of it ready for turning the outside. Will do that on the new lathe as it can mount directly on the screw thread so it will be concentric.
Jul 13, 2023 Completed turning the first cup chuck mount and turned the old cup chuck to fit. Made an aluminium spacer to lift the tool post to help make height adjustments.
Jul 14, 2023 Turned up the second cup chuck mount and 2 brass washers for the headstock shaft. Drilled the flange of the first cup chuck mount and fitted the wooden body. Trued it up and re-cut and burned the lines. Waxed the outside.
Jul 15, 2023 Cleaned up the parted off faces of the 2 large brass washers and opened up the holes slightly. Replaced the steel washers on the headstock shaft with them. Turned the recesses for the bearings in the treadle pulley wheel. Prepared 2 old cup-chucks for lead inserts.
Jul 16, 2023 Tried removing the toolpost mounting bolt to check it is just an m10. It is so the quick change toolpost I plan to buy will fit. Cast a thread insert in the smallest cup-chuck.
Jul 17, 2023 Cast another lead thread insert in one of the larger cup chucks. Drilled and tapped it.
Jul 18, 2023 Got the top plates for the tailstock and the thread cutting part of the headstock. Marked out the hole centres for the tailstock piece.
Jul 19, 2023 Drilled and tapped the square nut for the tailstock. Cut the recess for it. Drilled the top plate and filed up the edges. Drilled the tailstock for the top plate mounting bolts. I should have started doing the counterbores for the screw inserts with the piece bolted down. Drill (½inch) grabbed it and ripped it out of my hand and smacked it hard into the front door. No damage to the door or me and only a minor bash on the end of one of the beads, and a small chip that was caused by planing the surface that sits on the bedways and had been reglued is now missing.
Jul 20, 2023 Made the spacer blocks for the tailstock, drilled the hole for the dead centre, tapped the central hole and made a 12mm brass plug to avoid wear on the dead centre. Managed to line up the centres reasonably well.
Jul 21, 2023 Cleaned up the tailstock and oiled it.
Jul 22, 2023 Drawing designs for the oiler/bearing adjusters.
Jul 23, 2023 Cut a piece of 50mm brass and faced it ready for 2 more cup chuck bosses. Turned the 2 old cup chucks ready for the bosses.
Jul 24, 2023 Drilled and tapped the block. Parted it in 2 on the metal lathe, but had to finish off with a hacksaw, the parting tool isn't quite long enough. Turned the first boss by hand using the new lathe and the 6mm graver I made. Fitted it to the large circular cup chuck.
Jul 25, 2023 Tried to set up to film hand turning. I think I got mostly shots of the back of my shoulder. Will have to rethink it. Finished turning the boss for the square cup chuck.
Jul 26, 2023 Got the side plates of the treadle pulley wheel support made by Tuan. Bolted them together and started to file them up. Drilled the boss for the square cup chuck and mounted it.
Jul 27, 2023 Finished shaping the side plates. Some parts seem really hard so I used the grinder. Drilled out and tapped the top hole to take an M12 bolt.
Jul 28, 2023 Drilled out and tapped the bottom holes to take M8 bolts. Cut the wooden part to size.
Jul 29, 2023 Shaped the wooden part and drilled it. Fitted the metal sides. Removed the treadle and drilled that to match.
Jul 30, 2023 Fitted the treadle pulley support and connected the chain. Can't find my chain breaker but managed it with a pin punch. Treadle now working.
Aug 1,  2023 Started turning the grooves in the flywheel. Got some help from Pen and we managed to get the first groove cut. Welded the drive band (a bit too loose, but that's ok for now). Motor can now drive the flywheel, although I don't know how much power it can transmit.
Aug 2,  2023 Turned the inner edges and the sides if the wheel using the motor driving the headstock shaft, and the headstock shaft driving the flywheel. 
Aug 3,  2023 Removed the screws from the flywheel and completed turning the side of the wheel.
Aug 4,  2023 Replaced all the screws, got a couple of blisters doing it.
Aug 5,  2023 More turning of the left face of the flywheel, trying to get the screw heads flush.
Aug 6,  2023 Bought some 40 grit cloth backed abrasive paper and made a larger sanding block. More work on the left face of the flywheel. More to go though, will keep going until either the first screw heads start to appear smaller or all are flush.
Aug 7,  2023 Finished the left face of the flywheel. Sanded a few screw heads by hand, but most by using the 40grit block against the rotating wheel. Made a template to help turning the different steps and started turning them.
Aug 8,  2023 Completed turning the steps, and then the grooves in the flywheel.
Aug 9,  2023 Made the main part of thelocking bolt for the tailstock. Roughed out on the small lathe, but turned the dome on the new lathe using treadle drive. Started roughing out a piece of wood for the handles.
Aug 10, 2023 Started making a small brass cup chuck. Drilled the blank on the metal lathe and rough turned the outside and inside taper on the new lathe. I should probably have turned the recess at the same time as drilling it, turning it accurately proved too difficult.
Aug 11, 2023 Completed the brass cup shuck. All turned by leg power except for the initial hole for the thread. Used the cross slide to get the inside looking reasonably straight and true. Also cleaned up the outside with it. The hand turned suface was mostly better, apart from some small chatter marks, but the slide rest turned finish cleaned up well enough and looks straight. It has a parallel  section and a gentle taper in at the mouth end. Used the cup chuck to turn the first of the tailstock locking bolt handles. Not sure I like the shape, but it will do for now.
Aug 12, 2023 Completed the tailstock locking bolt. I still don't like it but not sure how I can change it... Fitted a bracket to hold the vernier calipers in the toolchest.
Aug 13, 2023 Altered the ends of the old mandrels so they can be carried in the brass cup chuck. Cut a piece of stone rosewood and started to turn it, hopefully an egg and a tool handle.
Aug 14, 2023 Turned an egg for mum. Roughed out the rest of the piece of stone rosewood ready for making a handle.
Aug 15, 2023 Started turning a small box for Nhâm. Mostly completed the wooden part.
Aug 16, 2023 Turned the brass lid for the box and completed the wooden part.
Aug 17, 2023 Modified a bolt for the toolrest. Turned off the head and reduced it to 10mm and cut a thread to attach the brass head. Visited Tuan and asked him to make me a cast iron stool.
Aug 18, 2023 Turned the brass bolt end and cut away the sides to locate in the tool rest banjo.
Aug 19, 2023 Turned a piece of brass for a nut to secure the toolrest. Driled and tapped it and cut the taper using a piece of bolt as a mandrel.
Aug 20, 2023 Started turning the handle pieces. Completed the first washer and ferule. This time the washer has a slight rebate so it locates properly in the end of the ferule. Rough turned the first handle including the steel threaded piece glued in.
Aug 21, 2023 Completed the first handle and turned the second. Fitted them to the tailstock locking bolt and put the ones from the there onto the toolrest securing nut as they are not quite so visible there.
Aug 22, 2023 Made a handle with the remaining piece of 1inch square stock. Cut some more ferules for more small handles and put some bolts and washers in vinegar to remove the zinc.
Aug 23, 2023 Blackened the bolts and one washer by heating to dull red using the gas cooker and quenching in oil. I think it is soya oil from earlier experiments to find a linseed substitute. Worked well. Left the rest of the washers in for a bit longer and put some wire in there too in preparation for silver soldering. Cut a piece of wood for the carrier poppet, squared it up and roughly marked it out.
Aug 24, 2023 Marked out the poppet accurately and sawed it out.
Aug 25, 2023 Shaped the poppet and cut out the recess for the bearing mount piece.
Aug 26, 2023 Turned the recess for the bearing shell in the offcut of the carrier poppet. Trued up the bottom of the poppet and drilled the second piece for 4 screws. Added the countersink inserts. Lined it up using the tailstock and a piece of stone rosewood destined for the turning gouge handle. Clamped the 2 pieces together ready for drilling.
Aug 27, 2023 Finished shaping the carrier poppet and oiled it.
Aug 28, 2023 Did some more drawings for the oiler/bearing-adjuster design. Ready to start making them at last. Drilled a pilot hole and fitted a ferrule on the piece of stone rosewood for the new turning gouge handle.
Aug 29, 2023 Completed and fitted the gouge handle. This stone rosewood is not so easy to turn. Came out ok in the end but it may not be a great choice for flutes.
Aug 30, 2023 Started planning the toolbox. Brought in some planks.
Aug 31, 2023 Cut 2 long pieces for the toolbox. Planed up a 3rd piece for the ends and started cleaning up one of the long pieces. Cut and sharpened a piece of HSS for a double sided marking knife to help in marking out the dovetails. No handle yet, I will try it without before trying to make a tang on HSS.
Sep 1,  2023 Planed face side and face edge of the long pieces of the lathe toolbox.
Sep 2,  2023 Cleaned up the ends of the long pieces and cut the 2 end pieces. Flattened the end pieces, there was still some cupping. Numbered all the joints and marked out the width of the matching piece and the dovetail tails.
Sep 3,  2023 Cut the tails.
Sep 4,  2023 Marked out and cut the pins. Fitted the first joint.
Sep 5,  2023 Fitted the remaining 3 joints and started looking for pieces to make the bottom. There should be just enough of Pen's old bookshelf left to do it.
Sep 7,  2023 Prepared pieces for the bottom of the lathe toolbox. 
Sep 8,  2023 Glued some of the pieces together. Started work on the oiler/adjusters. Drilled out some threaded rod and reduced one end of the first piece and cut a 10mm thread on it for the brass piece. Drilling on the metal lathe works best with an accurate centre. It's easy to break a carbide insert trying to turn this. Badly centred holes will cause problems when drilling from both ends. I managed to break a 3.2mm drill twice. First time it sheared off in the drill chuck so it was easy enough to remove. Second time it broke inside the piece. Not worth trying to dig it out, so I started again.
Sep 9,  2023 Glued another set of pieces together. Cut the 10mm thread on the end of the other oiler shank.
Sep 10, 2023 Glued the last set of pieces together. Cut the brass pieces for the oilers and drilled and tapped them to fit the shanks. Screwed the brass and steel pieces together and trued up the brass relative to the steel shanks. Bored out the top holes ready for the 14mm thread for the caps.
Sep 11, 2023 Cut most of the bottom pieces to the correct length. Cut the rebate for them in the box sides.
Sep 12, 2023 Tapered the thickness of the bottom pieces so they fit the slots. Put the box together without glue.
Sep 13, 2023 Glued up the lathe toolbox. Tapped the cups of the oiler/adjuster assemblies. Turned the beads down to size and roughed out the lower taper.
Sep 14, 2023 Cleaned up the lathe toolbox. Assembled the new tool trolley.
Sep 15, 2023 Rearranged the wood in the yard and moved the lathe a little for the tool trolley. Planed out the pieces to cut for the toolbox lid and started looking for pieces for the inner and lower trays.
Sep 16, 2023 Cut the 9 pieces for the lid of the lathe toolbox.
Sep 17, 2023 Re-drilled the bearing caps and tapped them M14. Drilled the oil holes in the top bearing shells. Oiler/adjusters are now functional.
Sep 18, 2023 Prepped face side and face edge of the pieces for the right hand section of the lathe toolbox lid.
