Oct 1,  2023 Fitted the other lid pieces and started to trip the mouldings to match.
Oct 2,  2023 Cleaned up the lid and the mouldings. Scraped, sanded and oiled the outside of the box.
Oct 3,  2023 Turned the curved parts of the oiler/adjuster bodies.
Oct 4,  2023 Annealed one of the cheap chisels I bought and filed it to shape for a beading tool. Hardened and tempered it. Had to do it twice, first time it ended up blue. Just used the gas cooker. It's a bit slow, a more powerful flame would be better but works ok on small stuff like this.
Oct 5,  2023 Made a handle for the beading tool.
Oct 6,  2023 Turned the boss for the indexer arm. Turned out the beading tool wasn't hardened properly. Re-filed it and hardened it again. Seems ok now. Also made a point tool which seems to work ok. The tang was soft enough to file. Ground the pointy end. Drilled and tapped the side hole in the indexer boss.
Oct 7,  2023 Turned the finial for the indexer. Drilled and tapped the indexer point block.
Oct 8,  2023 Completed turning the indexer point, and blackened it. Drilled the hole in the headstock to attach it. Put some washers, nuts and a bolt in vinegar to remove the plating. Not sure about the nuts, they may be stainless.
Oct 9,  2023 Fitted the indexer and filed the first of the bearing oiler-adjusters.
Oct 10, 2023 Filed the second oiler-adjuster.
Oct 11, 2023 Rough turned the cap for the first of the oilers. Some problems getting it to screw all the way home. A bottoming tap would have been useful.
Oct 12, 2023 Finished turning the first oiler cap. It wont screw home in the second oiler, whereas a slightly longer bolt will. I guess that means the bolt has more clearance. This will be a whole lot easier to handle when I have screwcutting ability on the lathe.
Oct 14, 2023 Turned and threaded the lower part of the second oiler cap on the metal lathe. Pressure from the tailstock is a good way of keeping the die reasonably square. Started turning the curved top on the new lathe.
Oct 15, 2023 Completed the acorn top for the second oiler. Shaped the first of the wing nuts. Started filing the screwcutting section top piece.
Oct 16, 2023 Made carriers for ¾inch pipe and 10 ferrules.
Oct 17, 2023 Made a new retaining plate for the tool rest. The one I was using was a little too thick and the bolt didn't go all the way through the nut. I thought this might be the cause of the thread getting stiffer, although it may have just been dirt. Also had a tidy up. Too much junk accumulating on the bench from a series of small jobs. Starting to be difficult to find stuff...
Oct 18, 2023 Made a handle for the long 5.5mm drill bit.
Oct 19, 2023 Made a handle for the long ½inch drill bit. Made a norrow point tool.
Oct 20, 2023 Made a handle for the square ended scraper.
Oct 21, 2023 Made 2 handles, one for the broad point tool and one for the triangular scraper. Oiled the flywheel except for the largest groove.
Oct 22, 2023 Finished the edges of the top plate of the screw cutting section. Drilled matching holes in the headstock. Oiled the rest of the flywheel and the pulley. Not sure that was a good idea but it should be ok once the oil dries.
Oct 23, 2023 Cut the block for the screw cutting assembly to depth and width. Drilled the holes for the bolts and the pilot hole for the main shaft.
Oct 24, 2023 Completed the screwcutting assembly housing and reassembled the headstock.
Oct 25, 2023 Made an octagonal handle from stone rosewood.
Oct 26, 2023 Ground the 10mm T spanner to make a square taper. Fitted the handle. Hit it too hard and split it, but not too badly. I should know that it only needs gentle taps to fit a handle. If it doesn't go on far enough, hitting it harder will not help.
Oct 27, 2023 Cut out the marking knife tang.
Oct 28, 2023 Made a handle for the marking Knife.
Oct 29, 2023 Made a wooden cover for the toolrest base to keep the swarf out of the slot.
Oct 30, 2023 Cut some brass and steel tube to make the headstock shaft end cap.
Oct 31, 2023 Faced off the 2 tubes and turned down the brass to fit inside the steel tube. First one was a bit loose so I made another. Cut the slot to fit the flats on the shaft. Realised the senral hole was a little to small so opened it up with the boring bar.
Nov 1,  2023 Tried to solder the parts together but ran out of gas. The solder had started to flow so I decided to risk continuing, but the joint separated in the final stages of turning the outside.
Nov 2,  2023 Cut new pieces for the headstock shaft end cap. Turned the outside of the brass to fit inside the steel piece. Reversed the headstock shaft and turned the section between the M14 thread and the two flats down to the 15mm it should have been. Just used the graver, it seems to work fine on steel.
Nov 3,  2023 Filed the flats on the inside of the brass piece and soldered them together. Used 2 torches, and this may be more than necessary. I melted the brass a bit. Looks like it wont be a problem though. The end cap now fits on the shaft, I just need to clean it up.
Nov 8,  2023 Trying to make a hair spike for Nham.
Nov 9,  2023 Made a second hair spike.
Nov 13, 2023 Made a handle for the 10mm long drill bit.
Nov 18, 2023 Planed and sawed a 2½ inch square piece of the yellowish wood I used for the lathe frame. Rough turned it. This wood is very dense, 950kg per m³ or thereabouts which is similar to boxwood. I have polished the endgrain in the past, just to see what it looks like and it is potentialy a reasonable substitute. The colour isn't quite the same and the grain may be a little more open but it is worth a try if I can find any crack free pieces.
Nov 19, 2023 Cut the piece of stone rosewood into 2 sections for the body and head joints. Together they were too long for the lathe. Rough turned the body section.
