Oct 22, 2024 Cut the thread on the screwcutting guide. Reassembled the headstock. Thread is not as even as I would like, there is skill needed to cut these well I think. Not bad for a first attempt, and hopefully good enough to work. Cutting a second one should be easier as I will be able to use the regular toolrest rather than the makeshift one bolted to the headstock. Cutting other pitches will be similarly tricky unless I can devise a jig to both mount the screwcutting guide blank and the master thread in the usual position.
Oct 23, 2024 Annealed a chisel blank and started filing it to make a 16tpi thread chaser. Marked the teeth out using a 16TPI tap and used a triangular file and a cold chisel to shape the teeth. Not easy and required many iterations but it is reasonably close when checked against the tap.
Oct 31, 2024 Cleaned up the screwcutting guide with the new thread chaser.
