Oct 14, 2025 Cut a piece of brass for the small square chuck. Faced it and drilled and tapped the centre hole. Used a boring bar to cut the shoulder relief. This meant changing the shims on the toolpost. Used the thick aluminium spacers under the toolpost and the 2 brown painted steel shims under the boring bar. The 2 steel spacers need to go back under the general purpose tool, and the U shaped spacer needs to replace the 2 thick aluminium spacers under the toolpost to return it to general purpose use.
